If the length of a simple pendulum is doubled, its period will
(A) decrease by 2
(B) increase by 2
(C) decrease by~$\sqrt{2}
(D) increase by~$\sqrt{2}

A rocket of mass m is launched with kinetic energy K\textsubscript{0~}from the surface of the Earth. How much less kinetic energy does the rocket have at an altitude of two Earth radii in terms of the gravitational constant, G; the mass of the Earth, m\textsubscript{E}; the radius of the Earth, R\textsubscript{E}; and the mass of the rocket?
(A) \dfrac{GM\_{E}m}{2R\_{E}}
(B) \dfrac{2GM\_{E}m}{3R\_{E}}
(C) \dfrac{3GM\_{E}m}{4R\_{E}}
(D) \dfrac{8GM\_{E}m}{9R\_{E}}
